"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The numpy.sinc function returns the normalized sinc function, which is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). For x=0, the result is 1, but for other integer values, the result is not necessarily 0. The assertions for sinc_result[1] == 0 is incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not equal to sinc(1)\\\"\"\n}"